{
  "text": "Viral infections and antibody treatments. For acute infections and to establish immunity, mice were infected i.p. with 1 \u03eb 10 5 PFU of Armstrong LCMVclE350 [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . For secondary viral infections at times \u05462 months after primary LCMV infection (\u05462 mpi), mice were i.v. challenged with 4 \u03eb 10 6 PFU of LCMVcl13 (18) or infected i.p. with 1 \u03eb 10 4 to 1.5 \u03eb 10 4 PFU of salivary gland-derived MCMV as previously described [CITATION_3] . For neutralization of IL-12, LCMV-immune mice were given 0.75 mg of either anti-IL-12p40 (clone C17.8) or an IgG2a isotype control (clone 2A3), both from BioXCell, at 12 h prior to infection with MCMV.",
